a regular Nonagon. Whereas, if the sides of the Nonagon are not equal, it i=
s called an irregular Nonagon.</p><p>The perimeter of the Nonagon is the to=
tal distance around the shape; so it is obtained by adding the length of th=
e sides. Generally, we measure it in units like centimeters, inches, meters=
, feet, etc.</p><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"how-to-use-the-nonagon=
