Perimeter (P)</strong> <br>The sum of lengths of the nine sides of the nona=
gon.</p><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"what-is-a-nonagon">What is a N=
onagon?</h2><p>A Nonagon is a nine-sided polygon. It is a closed two-dimens=
ional figure with nine interior and nine exterior angles.</p><p>The sum of =
all the interior angles will equal 1260 degrees, and all exterior angles wi=
ll equal 360 degrees.</p><p>Basically, Nonagons can be classified into four=
 types based on the length of their sides, a measure of their angles, and t=
heir vertices.</p><ol class=3D"wp-block-list"><li><strong>Regular Nonagon</=
strong>: if all nine sides of the Nonagon are equal and all nine angles are=
 equal, then the Nonagon is called a regular Nonagon.</li><li><strong>Irreg=
ular Nonagon</strong>: if the sides and the angles of the Nonagon are not e=
qual, then it is called an Irregular Nonagon.</li><li><strong>Convex Nonago=
n</strong>: if all of the vertices of the Nonagon point outward, then it is=
 called a Convex Nonagon.</li><li><strong>Concave Nonagon</strong>: if at l=
east one of the Nonagon=E2=80=99s vertex points inward, it is called a Conc=
ave Nonagon.</li></ol><p><strong>Properties of a Nonagon</strong></p><ol cl=
ass=3D"wp-block-list"><li>A Nonagon will have nine sides and nine angles.</=
